benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: DELETE /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/emails/{email} - Delete email from account

covered: Valid Request: Successful deletion scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC12, TC13, TC17, TC18, TC19) are well covered.
Non-Existent Resources: Tests for non-existent account (TC03) and non-existent email (TC04) are included.
Invalid Inputs: Tests for invalid accountId format (TC05), invalid email format (TC06), missing headers (TC07), and unsupported parameters (TC08) are present.
Error Handling: Unauthorized access (TC10), system errors (TC11), and service unavailability are tested.
Edge Cases: Very long email addresses (TC12), minimal-length email (TC13), and response time (TC14) are considered.
Concurrency: Multiple concurrent requests (TC15) are included.
Regression: Past bugs fixed (TC17, TC18) are covered.
Recovery: Transient network failure retry (TC19) is included.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with multiple emails or pagination scenarios.
Authorization: No explicit tests for unauthorized users or role-based access control beyond missing headers.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate or verify system behavior under high request volume or rate limiting.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test for caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify handling of accounts with many emails.
Include explicit authorization tests to ensure proper access control.
Implement rate limiting and throttling tests to verify system stability under load.
Add scenarios to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behavior.
